Once the eggs leave the mother\rquote s side they are left totally defenceless. At first, because of their bright yellow colour they are motionless preys, easy to spot. A great number of enemies await them. 
\par But mosquito eggs have an important characteristic. The colour of the eggs, which are laid at night, turns to black at first light. In this way they are well camouflaged from insects and birds. 
\par At the larval and pupal stages of some species of mosquito, such as the }{\i\f0\fs22\insrsid3626024\charrsid15433267 anopheles}{\f0\fs22\insrsid3626024\charrsid15433267 
