at in most cases it is not even felt. Then it finds the most appropriate place to pierce using a pair of devices located in the mouthpart, which are called \'93palpi.\'94 
\par The first incision is made with the upper and lower jaw. The four cutters in the sucking t
ube cut deep into the skin. The sensory organs of heat, smell, taste and touch play an important role in establishing where the capillaries are concentrated under the skin. After a few attempts the mosquito finds the vein.}{
